T1  - Beyond the Individual Victim: Linking Sexual Harassment, Team Processes, and Team Performance
AU  - Raver, Jana L.
AU  - Gelfand, Michele J.
Y1  - 2005/06/01
PY  - 2005
DA  - 2005/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amj.2005.17407904
DO  - 10.5465/amj.2005.17407904
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 387
EP  - 400
VL  - 48
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Previous sexual harassment research and theory have focused primarily upon the individual level, with little attention to team- or organization-level outcomes. In this article, we extend research on outcomes associated with sexual harassment to the team level with an examination of the relationships between team ambient sexual harassment, team conflict, team cohesion, team citizenship behaviors, and team financial performance. Practical implications and a multilevel model to guide future sexual harassment research are offered.
AB  - Previous sexual harassment research and theory have focused primarily upon the individual level, with little attention to team- or organization-level outcomes. In this article, we extend research on outcomes associated with sexual harassment to the team level with an examination of the relationships between team ambient sexual harassment, team conflict, team cohesion, team citizenship behaviors, and team financial performance. Practical implications and a multilevel model to guide future sexual harassment research are offered.
